<paragraph blockId="18.[2060,2655,306,733]" pageId="18" pageNumber="776">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2060,2216,306,339]" pageId="18" pageNumber="776">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Aellen, 1959" authorityName="Aellen" authorityYear="1959" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="776" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="inexspectatus">Pipistrellus inexspectatus Aellen, 1959</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation pageId="18" pageNumber="776">
“Ngaouyanga, vallée de la haute Benoué, 
<collectingCountry box="[2151,2306,389,418]" name="Cameroon" pageId="18" pageNumber="776">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
.”
</materialsCitation>
Pipustrellus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aellen" authorityYear="1959" box="[2215,2379,424,457]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="776" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="inexspectatus">inexspectatus</taxonomicName>
is probably closest to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[2160,2271,464,497]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="776" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuhlii">P. kuhlii</taxonomicName>
group of species. Records previously attributed to it from 
<collectingCountry box="[2505,2652,503,536]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="18" pageNumber="776">DR Congo</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[2127,2213,542,575]" name="Kenya" pageId="18" pageNumber="776">Kenya</collectingCountry>
are now attributed to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hill" baseAuthorityYear="1968" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="776" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eisentrauti">Hypsugo eisentrauti</taxonomicName>
. Specific epithet is often misspelled as inexpectatus. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
